  "UI_PATTERNS.md.hbs": "# UI Patterns & Styling Conventions — my-react-firebase-app
*Generated 2025-01-01 — v1.0.0-test*
This document details the interface standards, component rules, design system choices, and styling conventions for **my-react-firebase-app**.

---

## 🎨 Theme & Palette System

We target a premium visual identity:
- **Default**: Slate/Zinc scale with primary indigo accents.
- **Color Format**: Use HSL color declarations to simplify opacity adjustments and variations:
  - \`--primary\`: \`hsl(240, 5.9%, 10%)\`
  - \`--accent\`: \`hsl(263.4, 70%, 50.4%)\`
  - \`--background\`: \`hsl(0, 0%, 100%)\`

---

## 🧱 Component Layout Rules

- **Design Philosophy**: Use responsive, mobile-first design approaches.
- **Interactive States**: Every clickable component MUST have styling for:
  - \`:hover\` — slight scale-up (e.g. \`scale-102\`) or opacity adjustment.
  - \`:focus-visible\` — clean focus rings for accessibility.
  - \`:disabled\` — grayed out options, and \`cursor: not-allowed\`.

---

## 🌟 Modern Design Features

> [!TIP]
> ### Glassmorphism & Backdrop Filters
> Use modern CSS to build premium panel containers:
> \`\`\`css
> .glass-panel {
>   background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
>   backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
>   border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
> }
> \`\`\`
>
> ### Accessibility Checklist
> - Ensure all images have descriptive \`alt\` tags.
> - Contrast ratios should adhere to WCAG AA standards (minimum 4.5:1 for standard text).


---
*Documentation generated by [create-agent-docs](https://github.com/chesteralan/create-agent-docs) v1.0.0-test on 2025-01-01.*
